-- FCC, ACS to Compete in Tender for U.K. Bridge, Expansion Says
-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 2012-02-18T15:47:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/fcc-acs-to-compete-in-tender-for-u-k-bridge-expansion-says.html
Madrid-based builders Actividades de
Construccion y Servicios SA and Fomento de Construcciones &
Contratas SA are part of rival groups bidding to build the
Mersey Gateway Bridge in the U.K.,  Expansion  reported.  ACS unit Iridium will join with  Hochtief AG (HOT)  and  Galliford
Try Plc (GFRD) , while FCC is partnered by Bilfinger Berger SE and
Macquarie Infrastructure Co., the newspaper reported. Bouygues
SA is also bidding, and the project value is estimated at 842
million euros ($1.1 billion), Expansion said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
